Singer and actress Keabetswe KB Motsilanyane turned 37 last week Friday and to mark the occasion she celebrated with friends and fans at Basseline in Johannesburg. The singer said the day was special to her since its the first time she has celebrated publicly. I am so emotional about today and all the love people have shown me. My son was here today and saw me perform on stage for the first time. I am so happy, KB told DRUM soon after the show. Here is a look at snippets from the event; the singer was one of the loved faces that graced on soapie screens the time she was still acting on Rythm City on etv. The basseline is one of the renowned hot spots in johannesburg situated in newtown johannesburg , it has hosted a lot local acts as well international artists.